13/09/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The sixth congress of the opposition Socialist People's Party (SNP) will be held in Podgorica from November 19th-20th, according to a decision made on Sunday (September 12th). 
Delegates will discuss a new programme and party statute and will elect members of the main committee, as well as a new leader. 
The last SNP congress was held in 2006. 
(RTCG, Portal Analitika - 12/09/10)
